                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Tried soloing VaDynn tonight.  It's not possible using Centi's I don't believe.  They just die way to fast.  Shades and Golems are uncharmable.  I don't know if they're charmable, but if they are, I think it might be possible with some of IV's guards.  If they are charmable (which I intend to find out soon <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />   ) then it would definately be possible with a cleric Ching the pet.  
<br />

<br />
BTW....a trick for pulling VaDynn to the IZ solo....
<br />

<br />
Make you're way back to the shard chamber I talked about above.  Trigger and zone / clear all the traps between you and VaDynn (There's a trap in the hallway in front of VaDynn that I didn't put on the map because it's midway down the hall.)  Once the traps are triggered, pacify all the golems and shades between you and VaDynn.  Tag VaDynn with the Ceramic Band.  You want him to get damage agro on you, but not enough to cause him to summon.  Once agroed, run towards IZ.  If you have a raid, have them set up on one side, and pull to the other side.  VaDynn.  VD runs very slowly.  You will be agroing just about all the Centi between you and IZ, which is about 8-12.  Once you get to the end of the main hall, just before turning towards IZ, turn and charm the closest Centi to you, then hit F8, target the next closest Centi and sick your pet on him.  All the centi will stop and agro your pet, VaDynn will not and will continue following you to IZ.  Run to the zoneline opposite of where you're raid is, and when VaDynn finally catches up to you, zone out, run across to the other zoneline and zone back in while you're raid tags the now solo VaDynn at IZ.  
<br />

<br />
Another option (and I'm not sure if it works as I haven't tried it but will) is to Tag VaDynn with the Ceramic Band, then hit invisibility and run to Zone.  It's quite likely that you will get no adds at all by this method, but as I said, I'm not positive.   Good luck <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
